LANGUAGE SYSTEM

RiftsMUD uses a language system for in-game communication.  The 'say'
command broadcasts in your currently active language.  Players who do not
know that language hear garbled speech.

COMMANDS
  language <name>       switches your active spoken language
  languages             lists all languages you know and your skill levels
  say <text>            speaks aloud in your active language

HOW IT WORKS
  Each language has a skill percentage (0-98%).  When you speak a language,
  listeners who know the same language at 30%+ understand you normally.
  Listeners with lower skill hear partial garble.
  Listeners who do not know the language at all hear only alien sounds.

STARTING LANGUAGES
  Your character starts knowing their native racial language at 98% (native).
  OCCs that involve communication or military service may also start with
  American (the common trade tongue of post-Rifts North America) at high skill.

COMMON LANGUAGES
  American              the post-Rifts trade language (most humans know this)
  Dragonese / Elven     common among magic practitioners
  Techno-Can            used by the Coalition States military
  Gobblely              D-Bee trade language in many border settlements

